<sec id="id-6a64bb31-4715-4349-f952-01d7dc549d58"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="c5384817-554e-4c08-bd41-312ce2af6c8d" timestamp="1656534081076"?>Related actions and expectations<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c5384817-554e-4c08-bd41-312ce2af6c8d"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="34b31a0b-2724-4028-ec45-933d77690146" timestamp="1656534096132"?>The organization should:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="34b31a0b-2724-4028-ec45-933d77690146"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="ce959212-b2ad-4b8b-e3b0-ce58e54a415e" timestamp="1656534096132"?><list-item id="id-35fe2e89-9ac6-4b05-81d9-d89cc6e3b44b"><p>set up an editorial review committee to guarantee communications that are free of stereotypes and train the members of this committee in these questions, or train the communication unit in <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ce959212-b2ad-4b8b-e3b0-ce58e54a415e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="101adca7-2e10-420a-e5e7-cbb76ec907bf" timestamp="1670341396623"?>gender-<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="101adca7-2e10-420a-e5e7-cbb76ec907bf"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="78468fe4-7b65-48e1-a028-96cb51841d66" timestamp="1656534096132"?>inclusive communications free of gender biases;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-6e3897cb-64fa-41c0-917e-c0ac51f8943d"><p>define<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="78468fe4-7b65-48e1-a028-96cb51841d66"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="ab83d744-c827-4396-b986-befe9841f62d" timestamp="1669028092361"?> regular intervals suitable to the organisation's contexts (preferably every year), for its <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ab83d744-c827-4396-b986-befe9841f62d"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="25994cd9-e081-49ef-f5fa-ed0cdfdeb53a" text="an annual " timestamp="1669028067550"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="1e5420fb-a784-4941-e854-5530b8dbeeef" timestamp="1656534096132"?>internal and external communications plan on <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="1e5420fb-a784-4941-e854-5530b8dbeeef"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="6c781590-08df-4b72-a478-2b88e706cbff" timestamp="1670341413764"?>gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6c781590-08df-4b72-a478-2b88e706cbff"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="1c49c440-b276-4c47-d6ad-e3b97e8b3d8b" timestamp="1656534096132"?>equality, or include issues related to gender equality in the existing communications plans;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-619ecc1a-0dc6-453e-e5e2-f6bfba82dc14"><p>develop a non-sexist and without stereotypes communication in accordance with the organization’s gender equality policy;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-7ebea4eb-a2e3-4304-fbac-38cecf2c2914"><p>inform all the internal and external stakeholders of the organization’s gender equality policy, through accessible media and formats;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-cc6ed13a-74d2-4678-faf2-44b01709efd6"><p>disseminate and communicate the initiatives and results among stakeholders and the general public, creating awareness and valuing good practices on gender equality;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-d4cf162d-08eb-48b6-b79d-c3bedc2f4c51"><p>organize events and workshops, in particular on national or international days dedicated to subjects related to gender equality;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="1c49c440-b276-4c47-d6ad-e3b97e8b3d8b"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="51aa4e3c-4a3d-4829-9989-e5ceb1527a4f" text="organize events and workshops to raise awareness of stereotypes related to shareholding;" timestamp="1669033429227"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="b6148ba6-150e-45d7-e985-791e0f42f768" timestamp="1656534096132"?></p></list-item><list-item id="id-f0c5c930-2763-45fd-eb52-76e3c8d7ed78"><p>highlight the variety of the internal and external stakeholders on a regular basis (e.g., in an information newsletter);</p></list-item><list-item id="id-3f484b2c-341d-4aa0-8bd6-370eed34abf4"><p>take part in events in which the audience and the speakers are at least diverse, and preferably equal<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b6148ba6-150e-45d7-e985-791e0f42f768"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="cad1bafa-4314-4fa0-efc2-8a7b003158df" text="." timestamp="1667318574765"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="f62218e9-757b-4b9f-c9f9-581109c65b03" timestamp="1667318575648"?>;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f62218e9-757b-4b9f-c9f9-581109c65b03"?></p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="00d4ac83-a94a-47ab-ea6d-8c32f54bd352" timestamp="1656534125029"?><list-item id="id-4a20fa43-890c-48b0-9c57-1d89af9038c0"><p>give a gender equality welcome kit to all new stakeholders (e.g., the internal policy in favour of equality, information on specialized organizations, the support provided by the organization that enables the stakeholders to fulfil their family responsibilities, etc.);</p></list-item><list-item id="id-c007361b-366a-466b-8e84-c3e9fc86932b"><p>create a virtual or physical space where the rights of its employees with regard to equality are set forth, and the numbers of the specialized associations and any other information on the prevention of sexual and gender-based violence are provided<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="00d4ac83-a94a-47ab-ea6d-8c32f54bd352"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="4bc7f9e3-1206-4868-9023-a1edd45939ee" text="." timestamp="1667318579386"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="23c983e8-c231-4df9-f2fb-a6e89bd7c057" timestamp="1667318579853"?>;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="23c983e8-c231-4df9-f2fb-a6e89bd7c057"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="db91eb57-7ef1-4069-c641-beeae5a07f31" timestamp="1656534125029"?></p></list-item><list-item id="id-7b333eba-3cd9-45a3-f755-2b471d11574c"><p>guarantee the <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="db91eb57-7ef1-4069-c641-beeae5a07f31"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="3e44dd01-5bf4-45ec-cde1-3e7e7064c5aa" text="diversity" timestamp="1668699208002"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="74762c9e-5237-4e14-ca57-177598201cc5" timestamp="1668699209107"?>parity<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="74762c9e-5237-4e14-ca57-177598201cc5"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="2a44a4dc-0ea2-4c6d-a915-934a54bef1f9" timestamp="1656534125029"?> of the names given to its physical and virtual spaces;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-2a9dab49-e5ac-4de6-e049-53b9646b4676"><p>organize or participate in awards and competitions that reward persons or organizations whose work or personal initiative promotes gender equality;</p></list-item><list-item id="id-9106bb10-e89b-4683-9757-eac51534ef82"><p>take actions to <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2a44a4dc-0ea2-4c6d-a915-934a54bef1f9"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="07426ce5-838d-44f9-d4ca-07de0a55c9b4" text="promot" timestamp="1669034102032"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="44560eaa-8e30-438f-d877-e1fd3d14de44" timestamp="1656534125029"?>e<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="44560eaa-8e30-438f-d877-e1fd3d14de44"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="87b8a31c-8a6a-49ab-abf7-f36df9c4ea89" timestamp="1669034103282"?>ncourage<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="87b8a31c-8a6a-49ab-abf7-f36df9c4ea89"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="3c516463-2d4b-4fc5-9672-0abdf5c5d4c6" timestamp="1656534125029"?> women<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3c516463-2d4b-4fc5-9672-0abdf5c5d4c6"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="a6d9b06d-06c3-4762-b198-849fc0b579f3" timestamp="1669034202226"?>'s<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a6d9b06d-06c3-4762-b198-849fc0b579f3"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="882150ed-3468-4b4a-c531-791640ae66fc" timestamp="1656534125029"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="882150ed-3468-4b4a-c531-791640ae66fc"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="adb419a1-d034-403c-c35a-fa2ede894904" timestamp="1669034205061"?>empowerment <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="adb419a1-d034-403c-c35a-fa2ede894904"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="1089d540-8a4b-4d3d-fa6c-213eba96b232" text="wh" timestamp="1669034121960"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="4179b5a5-27c3-4113-ccc1-2a319f08b7e9" timestamp="1669034122279"?>t<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4179b5a5-27c3-4113-ccc1-2a319f08b7e9"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="1961f132-8ccc-4e5a-d493-c83bd9c2d5fd" timestamp="1656534125029"?>o work in professions and activities that are predominantly masculine, and men who work in professions and activities that are predominantly feminine.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="1961f132-8ccc-4e5a-d493-c83bd9c2d5fd"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="21871fde-a781-40ac-ecab-a0984b8a6120" timestamp="1670341500149"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="21871fde-a781-40ac-ecab-a0984b8a6120"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="5d0c464f-89ab-4936-eabb-5aab20a45de2" timestamp="1669035207833"?><italic>NOTE: Research indicates that men employed in traditionally feminine fields average higher salaries than their female colleagues and are often promoted more quickly and with less experience than their female colleagues. A requirement to promote men in traditional women’s industries may be redundant in its effects. <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://doi.org/10.1177/09500172004042773" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://doi.org/10.1177/09500172004042773</ext-link><ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://nces.ed.gov/surveys/sass/tables/sass1112_2013313_p1s_002.asp" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://nces.ed.gov/surveys/sass/tables/sass1112_2013313_p1s_002.asp</ext-link><ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11199-014-0419-z" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">https://doi.org/10.1007/s11199-014-0419-z</ext-link></italic></p></list-item></list><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5d0c464f-89ab-4936-eabb-5aab20a45de2"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="619e0edd-76b6-4ed3-da71-de3817bf1002" text="Note 1 to entry" timestamp="1670261708360"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8954503" change-id="38039e86-8e2e-4f03-c4e9-ee46abd8fdc4" text="." timestamp="1666864874468"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="c8fa9158-ea70-4dce-d04a-b2dba5f212c0" text="diversDiversi" timestamp="1666858987822"?><p/><p/></sec>